<HEADLINE> Newspaper Editorial on Chinese Communist Party Anniversary (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The People's Daily newspaper has
called for the building up of the Party's power and greatness, in
an editorial to be published on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The editorial stresses that the speech made by Communist Party
of China (CPC) Central Committee General Secretary and Chinese
President Jiang Zemin at a forum on June 28 marking the 78th
anniversary of the founding of the CPC is a guideline for thus
building up the Party in these new, exciting and interesting times.
</P>
<P>
It says that Jiang's speech is highly instructive for both
improving the Party and pushing forward the reform, opening up and
modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
Jiang emphasized in his speech that an extensive education
drive in theoretical study, political awareness and expecting good
conduct among government officials above the county level is a
prevailing priority of the Party at present.
</P>
<P>
The editorial sums up in one dynamic sentence the long and
glorious, if somewhat tortuous, history of the CPC as it drove
forward the revolutionary and construction course of the country:
"The key lies in the Party." It insists that without the CPC,
there would never have been a new China, the growth of socialism,
the great achievements of the reform, opening up and modernization
drive, or the bright prospects now facing the country and the
people.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990701.0007 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Newspaper Editorial on Chinese Communist Party Anniversary (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The editorial goes on to emphasize that political awareness is
at the core of the education drive.
</P>
<P>
"The politics that we are talking about is concrete and pure,"
it says.
</P>
<P>
It goes on to elaborate that political awareness refers to "
reinforcing the correct ideals and beliefs," "for party members to
be good at correctly recognizing and assessing situations in terms
of politics," "to be able to maintain a cool mind and a firm and
basic political line on wide-ranging issues, guidelines and
policies," "consciously able to adhere to the Party's principle of
democratic centralism," and "whole-heartedly serve the interests
of the people."
</P>
<P>
"Above all, every party member and cadre, and especially the
leaders, should raise their political awareness, no matter in
which field and on which front he or she works," it says.
</P>
<P>
It calls for party members to learn modern sciences, because "
communists are outstanding individuals who are armed with the most
advanced achievements of human civilization."
</P>
<P>
Noting that today's international competition means there will
be constant tests for the leadership of all countries in terms of
governmental skills and capabilities, the editorial says that
China's Communist Party members have a duty to work harder to make
the Party and the country stronger and more powerful. 
</P>
</TEXT>
