<HEADLINE> Obasanjo Swears in New Nigerian Government </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Nigerian President Olusegun Obasanjo
 swore in his civilian government in capital Abuja Wednesday after
a one-month wait since he took office on May 29 this year.
</P>
<P>
The ministers Obasanjo appointed last week took their turns in
taking the oath.
</P>
<P>
Sule Lamido became the Foreign Minister of the first civilian
government after some 15 years of military rule in the most
populous African country.
</P>
<P>
Adamu Ciroma became Finance Minister while General Theophilus
Danjuma took the portfolio of the Ministry of Defense.
</P>
<P>
Dapo Sarumi was appointed as Information Minister, Lyorchia Ayu
as Minister of Industry, Sani Zango Daura as Minister of
Agriculture and Tunde Adeniran as Education Minister, the
president announced.
</P>
<P>
Obasanjo also announced the names of 24 ministers and 20
ministers of state. 
</P>
</TEXT>
