<HEADLINE> Angola Has Highest Maternal Mortality: U.N. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The maternal mortality rate in
Angola is 2, 800 per 100,000 pregnant women, the highest in the
world, the U.N. Fund for Population Activities (UNFPA) said here
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
UNFPA technical counsel Joao Bosco Feres revealed this at a
function to mark the World Population Day which falls on July 11.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. official attributed the high mortality to infections
caused by inappropriate birth methods and care.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Feres pointed out that teenage mothers also
attributed to the high mortality, saying that many young women
aged 16 or 17 years have given more than two births.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. official noted his fund will exert its effort to
reduce maternal mortality and improve the living conditions of
women, especially the mothers.
</P>
<P>
He also asked the Angolan government to play its part in this
regard. 
</P>
