<HEADLINE> 24 Feared Dead in Boat Accident in Lake Malawi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-four people are
feared to have drowned after a boat capsized in Lake Malawi in
east Africa, the Tanzanian police said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The boat, with more than 30 passengers on board, capsized in a
water territory of the Kyela district, southwest Tanzania's Mbeya
Region at 9:00 pm Monday night, the police said.
</P>
<P>
Laurian Sanya, the Mbeya regional police commander, said over
telephone that there was a storm when the incident happened. He
added that 11 people were rescued.
</P>
<P>
Tanzanian Prime Minister Frederick Sumaye has sent a message
of condolence to Mbeya Regional Commissioner Basil Mramba
following the tragedy.
</P>
<P>
Sumaye said he was profoundly shocked to hear the incident as
so many people were killed. 
</P>
