<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Leaders of Integrity Urged for Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan State Minister of Internal
Affairs Sarah Kiyingi said Africa lacks leaders of integrity and
this hinders the development of the continent.
</P>
<P>
The minister made the remarks here Wednesday, Radio Uganda
reported in its evening report.
</P>
<P>
She said African leaders do not mentor their successors, thus
leading to the lack of upright and successful leaders.
</P>
<P>
The continent has been involved in wars and conflicts over the
last 30 years, which resulted in the degeneration of values, the
minister said while officiating a leadership dinner.
</P>
<P>
This partly explains the backwardness of the continent, she
noted.
</P>
<P>
The incorrect decisions made by such leaders add to people's
untold suffering and rampant corruption among senior government
officials.
</P>
<P>
The minister called for leaders of the continent to pay more
attention to the integrity of leaders at various levels, saying
this is the only way out for Africa. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
