<HEADLINE> NATO to Remain in Albania Till Aid Mission Ends </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, June 30 (Xinhua) -- NATO forces will stay in Albania
till its aid mission ends, a NATO officer said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
NATO forces will continue to help Albania reconstruct roads and
other infrastructure facilities in accordance with the agreement
signed between NATO and Albania, Colonel Volfgang Greven was
quoted as saying by the Albanian Telegraphic Agency (ATA).
</P>
<P>
NATO forces are revamping some road segments in Albania,
including one to Rinas Airport, one on the Durres-Kukes road, said
the officer who worked at the headquarters of the NATO forces in
Albania.
</P>
<P>
NATO forces "on humanitarian mission" began to operate in
Albanian about two months ago and the contingent currently
embraces some 7,000 persons from NATO's 19 member countries, ATA
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
