<HEADLINE> Stoichkov Quits Japan's Kashiwa Reysol </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Bulgarian World Cup star Hristo
Stoichkov has quit the Japanese professional club Kashiwa Reysol.
</P>
<P>
The 33-year-old Stoichkov told the club that his desire to play
soccer has declined and that the distance between Bulgaria and
Japan caused him family problems.
</P>
<P>
The top scorer in the 1994 World Cup moved to Reysol from
Bulgaria's CSKA Sofia team in July 1998. He scored 12 goals for
Kashiwa. 
</P>
