<HEADLINE> Eastern China City to Host Small Goods Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 1 (Xinhua) -- A national fair displaying small
goods will be held in the city of Yiwu in the central part of east
China's Zhejiang Province, from October 8-12.
</P>
<P>
At a press conference held here Wednesday, a local governmental
official said that about 800 Chinese and foreign companies and
wholesale and retail dealers in the fashion, food, light industry,
and department store sector are expected to display their products
during the fair, the fifth of its kind.
</P>
<P>
"During the fair, the city will host a seminar on the
development of industrial wholesale markets in China and an
investment attraction fair," the official said.
</P>
<P>
"The 500,000-square meter China Small Commodities Market, which
was set up in 1982 in Yiwu, now has an average of 26,000 traders
and shoppers and receives 150,000 customers every day," the
official said, adding that last year's fair attracted 694
companies from 13 countries worldwide and reached more than 2.86
billion yuan in sales.
</P>
<P>
The city has close relations with Shanghai as some 12 percent
of its market commodities come from the city.  
</P>
</TEXT>
