<HEADLINE> Share Prices Surge on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Share Prices closed sharply
higher on Singapore Stock Market Thursday, buoyed by the strong
overnight performance on Wall Street following the U.S. Fed's
decision to adopt a neutral monetary policy.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) shot up 47.05 points to
close at 2,214.75.
</P>
<P>
Total volume was about 1.591 billion shares valued at 1.894
billion Singapore dollars (1.114 billion U.S. dollars). Gainers
led losers by 261 to 77 with 107 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
SinSoonH was the most active stock with a turnover of 113.28
million shares. It was followed by AFP which had 80.3 million
units done. Summit was next with 65.78 million counters changing
hands.
</P>
<P>
Venture topped gainers of the day running up 330 cents to close
at 13.2 Singapore dollars. SPH gained 100 cents to finish at 30
Singapore dollars. CityDev rose 70 cents to end at 11.6 Singapore
dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, DBS was the biggest loser of the day with a
loss of 40 cents at 17.8 Singapore dollars. NatElec lost 25 cents
to finish at 7.2 Singapore dollars and DBS F shed 20 cents to
finish at 22.8 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that with support from firm institutional buying,
blue chips were broadly higher but small capitalized stocks
continued to dominate turnover.
</P>
<P>
They noted that the sentiment gained momentum after the U.S.
Federal Open Market Committee refrained from taking a tight
monetary policy bias.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. Federal Reserve also raised its federal funds rate by
25 basis points, a move widely expected by the market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
