<DOCNO> XIE19990701.0122 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ukraine to Cut Premier Side to 14 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The Ukrainian Professional Football
League (UPFL) has decided to reduce the number of teams in the
premier division from 16 to 14 in next season.
</P>
<P>
League secretary Dmitro Reznik said on Thursday the reduction
was necessitated by the large increase in the number of games for
top clubs like Dynamo Kiev.
</P>
<P>
The new season begins on July 12, just 16 days after the end of
the 1999-2000 campaign. 
</P>
</TEXT>
