<HEADLINE> S.Korean Police Cracks Down on Illegal Firearms Owners </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The South Korean police Thursday
launched a one-month crackdown on owners of illegal firearms.
</P>
<P>
Police will intensively check the manufacture and sale of
homemade firearms, and strike hard at illegal weapons dealing near
U.S. military bases, airports and harbors and illegal possession
of firearms.
</P>
<P>
Crimes in which firearms were used totaled 223 in the first
half of this year, 42 of them involving murder, robbery, rape,
theft and violence, said the National Police Agency.
</P>
<P>
Increased firearms had been smuggled into South Korea from
abroad and their circulation was on the rise, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
Police confiscated 201 illegal firearms in the first six months
of this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
