<HEADLINE> Pankratov Included in Russian Team despite Poor Performance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Dual Olympic butterfly champion
Denis Pankratov made the Russian team for this month's European
swimming championships to be held in Istanbul in spite of poor
performance at the national competition.
</P>
<P>
The 25-year-old, who won the 100 and 200-meter events in 1996,
fell far behind the qualifying standard set by the Russian
Swimming Federation, but he was still named in the 32-strong team
for the championships.
</P>
<P>
Pankratov came a distant third in the 100 with a time of 54.69
seconds, losing by more than a second to Anatoly Polyakov.
</P>
<P>
He was beaten again by Polyakov in the 200, with a
disappointing 1:59.35, more than four seconds off his world record
of four years ago. 
</P>
