<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 10 Tamil Rebels Killed in Northern Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan government troops
Wednesday killed 10 Tamil rebels in separate clashes in Northern
Province, the Defense Ministry announced Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Government troops on a limited operation were fired upon by
Tamil rebels with machine guns and small arms in general area
Paranthan on Sunday morning. The troops retaliated and killed at
least four rebels, military spokesman R.P. Witana said.
</P>
<P>
Witana said troops sniped and killed one rebel in the northwest
of Paranthan on the morning.
</P>
<P>
Around 6:15 p.m. Sunday in general area Paranthan, troops
confronted a group of rebels with small arms and machine guns.
Ground troops confirmed that three rebels were killed, he said.
</P>
<P>
On the same day, troops operating ahead of defenses north of
Mankulam sniped and killed two rebels, Witana added.
</P>
<P>
Tamil rebels have been fighting the Sri Lankan government since
1983 for an independent Tamil homeland in the north and east of
the country. Tens of thousands of people have been killed in the
armed conflict. 
</P>
</TEXT>
