<HEADLINE> Military Scientists Urged to Make More Contributions to National Defense </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Jiang Zemin, General Secretary of
the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC), has
urged military scientists to solve a range of major technological
problems in the field of national defense in order to catch up
with the rest of the world.
</P>
<P>
He made the call in a letter to the Commission of Science,
Technology and Industry for National Defense, as well as a number
of military supply industrial groups, on June 28.
</P>
<P>
At the same time Jiang welcomed the restructuring of the
sector from five core groups into ten, more efficient and
independently controlled corporations serving national defense.
</P>
<P>
Jiang stressed that the move was an important part of the
country's overall modernization program which was also aimed at
boosting national defense.
</P>
<P>
Scientists involved in military work are urged to stick to the
spirit of "self-reliance, hard struggle and selflessness devotion"
and make coordinated efforts in their scientific research in the
field of national defense.
</P>
<P>
The General Secretary called on them to work closely together
much like their predecessors had done when developing the atomic
and hydrogen bombs and satellites decades ago.
</P>
<P>
During the overall push to build socialism with Chinese
characteristics, China must continuously promote the economic
growth and power of national defense, Jiang said. He also called
on party committees, governments at various levels and all
branches of the People's Liberation Army (PLA) to actively support
the national defense industry.
</P>
<P>
The newly established military industrial groups are also asked
to introduce administrative and management reforms to meet the
demands of the socialist market economy.
</P>
<P>
Technical innovation of the national defense industry is also
urged by Jiang Zemin.  
</P>
</TEXT>
