<HEADLINE> Nigeria Aim at Taking Revenge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
SAN JOSE, June 30 (Xinhua) -- One day before their quarterfinals
against Brazil, the Nigerian team have already aimed at taking
revenge to the American team.
</P>
<P>
The Nigerian team suffered a 7-1 loss to the American team in
group competitions, but they still managed to qualify for the
quarterfinals with a 2-1 win over DPR Korea and 2-0 over Denmark.
</P>
<P>
On making the quarterfinals, Nigerian coach Ismaila Mabo said:"I
am highly delighted to have done not only Nigeria but the continent
of Africa proud."
</P>
<P>
Mabo didn't give up hopes of making the final:"With God on our
side, we shall qualify for the finals and play against the United
States and also take our revenge."
</P>
<P>
But the Nigerians' next opponents will be the Brazilians and
Mabo said he knew the Brazilian soccer style well:"In my playing
days, I played under a Brazilian coach in Nigeria. I know the style
of Brazil and I am going to present a very good strategy that will
counter the smooth play of Brazil."
</P>
<P>
"We will win the match against Brazil on Thursday. After our
next match against Brazil, I will start to think about the U.S.
team." said Mabo.
</P>
<P>
Nigerian forward Mercy Akide said:"I know victory shall be ours.
 And after that I will start thinking about the American team."
</P>
<P>
Brazilian coach Wilson De Oliveira Rica also set his aim on
playing the American team in the semifinals, but he said he would
not underestimate any one of their opponents:"We will respect every
single one of our opponents. There is no preference to play any
team. We will prepare like we always prepare."
</P>
<P>
Rica said:"Inevitably we will have to face the U.S. team and
down the road is much better because teams will have sharpened up
their skills." 
</P>
</TEXT>
