<HEADLINE> China's Stand on WTO Entry Unchanged </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 1 (Xinhua)-- China's stand on entering the World
Trade Organization (WTO) remains unchanged, said Zhang Qiyue,
spokeswoman of the Chinese Foreign Ministry here today.
</P>
<P>
"Due to the attack on Chinese embassy in Yugoslavia by the U.S.-
led NATO, the Sino-U.S. relationship has encountered some
difficulties," said the spokeswoman at a routine press conference
this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
"Thus, the atmosphere surrounding the bilateral negotiation on
China's entry into WTO has also been affected, and it is very
difficult, therefore, for the two sides to undertake conscientious
negotiations in this regard," Zhang added. 
