<HEADLINE> Facts and Figures: China's Trade With Major European Partners </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The following are facts and figures
on China's trade with major partners in Europe for the first five
months this year, provided by the General Administration of
Customs:
</P>
<P>
Total trade volume with Germany reached 5.872 billion US
dollars, up 16 percent from the same period last year. China's
exports to Germany hit 2.856 billion US dollars, up 3.8 percent.
Imports from Germany reached 3.017 billion US dollars, up 30.5
percent.
</P>
<P>
Total trade volume with Britain topped 2.696 billion US dollars,
up 10.8 percent. China exports to Britain declined 5.8 percent to
1.608 billion US dollars, while imports from Britain surged 49.7
percent to 1.086 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Total trade volume with France surged 30 percent to 2.445
billion US dollars, with China's exports to France at 1.069
billion US dollars, up 11.2 percent, and imports from France up 67
percent to 1.376 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Total trade volume with the Netherlands reached 2.319 billion
US dollars, down 1.4 percent. While China's exports to the
Netherlands reached 1.959 billion US dollars, down 3.6 percent,
China's imports from the Netherlands rose 12.3 percent to 359.153
million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Total trade volume with Russia climbed 0.7 percent to 2.257
billion US dollars. While China's exports to Russia plummeted 51.2
percent to 430.95 million US dollars, China's imports from Russia
surged 34.4 percent to 1.826 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Total trade volume with Italy reached 2.080 billion US dollars,
up 9.6 percent, with China's exports to Italy up 6.6 percent at 1.
099 billion US dollars, and imports from Italy up 13.1 percent at
980.896 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Total trade volume with Sweden reached 1.090 billion US dollars,
up 50.4 percent. China's exports to Sweden dropped 14 percent to
224.279 million US dollars, and imports from Sweden surged 86.7
percent at 865.801 million US dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
