<HEADLINE> Thailand, China Sign Medicine Cooperation Accord </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Thailand and China signed two
agreements here Thursday on a joint research in the use of herbal
medicine to treat cancer and AIDS.
</P>
<P>
The cooperation will be carried out between the Kunming
Institute of Botany (KIB) of the Chinese Academy of Sciences and
the Public Health Ministry of Thailand.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreements, the Chinese side will be in charge of the
research of pharmaceutics and pharmacology while the Thai side
will carry out research in clinical practice.
</P>
<P>
Both sides expressed the will that through close cooperation,
the two countries may obtain a larger share of the world market of
natural medicine.
</P>
<P>
The signing ceremony was part of the activities celebrating the
24th anniversary of the establishment of diplomatic relations
between Thailand and China. 
</P>
