<BODY>
<HEADLINE> German Insurance Group Enters Israeli Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, July 1 (Xinhua) -- German insurer Gerling Credit
Group has acquired a 20 percent stake in a subsidiary of Clal
Insurance, the second largest insurance company in Israel, the
Jerusalem Post daily reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
One of the leading international credit insurance groups with
subsidiaries in Europe, North America and Australia, Gerling is
the first overseas company to enter the Israeli credit insurance
market.
</P>
<P>
Under an agreement, Clal Credit Insurance, which provides
insurance protection to Israeli exporters, will use Gerling's
services in underwriting risks in foreign markets, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
The subsidiary of Clal Insurance said that the agreement will
enable it to expand operations in both domestic and overseas
markets.
</P>
<P>
French insurance Company Coface, the world leader in export
credit insurance, is also examining the possibility of entering
the Israeli market, the paper said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
