<HEADLINE> Facts and Figures: China's Trade with EU, ASEAN, APEC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The following are the facts and
figures about China's foreign trade with the ASEAN, EU and APEC
for the first five months of the year, provided by the General
Administration of Customs:
</P>
<P>
China's total trade volume with the Association of Southeast
Asian Nations (ASEAN) grew 10.2 percent to 9.852 billion US
dollars. While China's exports to ASEAN reached 4.258 billion US
dollars, up 3.3 percent, imports from ASEAN surged 16.1 percent to
5.594 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Total trade volume between China and the European Union reached
20.195 billion US dollars, up 16.7 percent. Exports to the EU
climbed 0.6 percent to 10.774 billion US dollars and imports from
the EU surged 42.8 percent to 9.421 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
China total trade volume with Asia Pacific Economic Cooperation
(APEC) nations hit 96.217 billion US dollars, up 2.0 percent.
While China's exports to APEC nations declined 6.4 percent to 49.
351 billion US dollars, imports grew 12.7 percent to 46.866
billion US dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
