<HEADLINE> Chinese Coach Satisfied With Team's Performance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
SAN JOSE, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Chinese coach Ma Yuanan was quite
satisfied with his team's performance in the quarterfinal match
against Russia and vowed to fight to the end of the tournament.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese team dominated the match and beat Russia 2-0 to book
a berth in the semifinals slated for July 4 at Boston.
</P>
<P>
The result equalled the Chinese team's best record in the World
Cup tournaments. They finished fifth in the inaugural World Cup
held in China in 1991 and placed fourth in Sweden four years ago.
</P>
<P>
Ma Yuanan said after his team's victory over Russia:"I am very
pleased with our performance today. This is a game of life and
death. So if we don't want to pack our luggage for Beijing earlier
in the tournament, we should fight to the last minute."
</P>
<P>
"This game is about our techniques, strategies and mental
toughness. The game is cruel. Any team that loses can't play the
next game. The Chinese players are quite stable today." Ma said.
</P>
<P>
Ma said his players were not nervous at the beginning of the
match:"I think we did pretty good from the beginning. We missed
some chances. We shall improve on that in the future."
</P>
<P>
Ma said it made no difference to him if China play Sweden or
defending champions Norway:"No matter which team win, it's not a
problem to us. In 1998, we played against Norway three times and we
won twice and lost one game. Since 1995 we have not lost to Sweden.
To me, the important thing is we have to play our best."
</P>
<P>
Norway beat Sweden 3-1 in another quarterfinal match later on
Wednesday. China and Norway will vie for a berth in the final at
Boston on July 4. 
</P>
</TEXT>
