<HEADLINE> Myanmar Newspaper Urges More Interchanges With China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The official newspaper New Light of
Myanmar Thursday said that the peoples of Myanmar and China will
enjoy fruits of interchanges through the promotion of economic
cooperation between the two nations.
</P>
<P>
In its editorial titled "Enhancing Bilateral Economic
Cooperation", the newspaper quoted Lieutenant-General Khin Nyunt,
first secretary of the Myanmar State Peace and Development Council
(SPDC), as saying that he had "successful" discussions with
Chinese leaders during his recent visit to Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Khin Nyunt, who visited China from June 7 to 11 at the
invitation of Chinese State Councilor Luo Gan, said the
discussions were held "with a constructive approach and
understanding."
</P>
<P>
Khin Nyunt, accompanied by a deputy prime minister and eight
other ministers, said his visit is aimed at strengthening the
existing friendship and further promoting the mutually beneficial
economic cooperation between the two countries, and studying the
advances made by China in national development endeavors.
</P>
<P>
At the recent third coordination meeting of Myanmar's Leading
Committee for the Promotion of Economic Cooperation Between
Myanmar and China, Khin Nyunt also said that he had cordial
discussions with the Chinese leaders on the implementation of
tasks under the bilateral economic cooperation programs.
</P>
<P>
The committee was formed after Senior General Than Shwe,
Myanmar SPDC chairman, paid a state visit to China in January
1996.
</P>
<P>
Since a long time ago, there have been cordial and friendly
relations between Myanmar and China with frequent exchange of
visits by their leaders. Over the past 10 years, the two countries
have also enhanced relations in the economic field. 
</P>
</TEXT>
