<HEADLINE> China's Wang Picked by Dallas Mavericks in NBA Draft </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Chinese center Wang Zhizhi has
been picked 36th in the second round of the National Basketball
Association draft to become the first Chinese drafted by the NBA.
</P>
<P>
Wang, who is 2.12 meters tall and weighs 115 kilograms,
averaged 11.1 points and 5.6 rebounds for China at the Atlanta
Olympic Games in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Wang, who turns 22 on July 8, plays for China's five-time
national champion Bayi Rockets.
</P>
<P>
He led China's CBA league by blocking last season and was third
in scoring. 
