<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Pakistani Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Pakistani English newspapers Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The News:
</P>
<P>
-- In a major success to further bring down morale of the
Indian Air Force and sending shocking waves across the Indian
military leadership, one Indian front-line attacking jet "Jaguar"
was shot down early Wednesday morning near the Line of Control in
Kashmir.
</P>
<P>
The Nation:
</P>
<P>
-- Pakistan's military said Wednesday Indian war planes had
intruded into Pakistani territory in the disputed Kashmir region
for the second time in four days and warned of possible action
against any such future flights.
</P>
<P>
The Frontier Post:
</P>
<P>
-- Pakistan is ready to talk to India at any forum for a
peaceful solution of all outstanding disputes but Indian military
build-up can jeopardize the lives of 1.3 billion people of the
Sub-continent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
