<DOCNO> XIE19990701.0231 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hu Jintao Attends Monument Unveiling Ceremony in HK (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 1 (Xinhua) -- A grand ceremony for the
unveiling of the Monument in Commemoration of the Return of Hong
Kong to China was held here Thursday morning to mark the second
anniversary of Hong Kong's return to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-President Hu Jintao extended warm congratulations
on the occasion on behalf of the central government and the people
of various nationalities of the country. He also extended festival
regards and greetings to the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region (HKSAR) government, Hong Kong compatriots and personages of
various walks of life.
</P>
<P>
At 08:40, Vice-President Hu Jintao and HKSAR Chief Executive
Tung Chee Hwa pulled the colored strings to unveil the 20-meter-
high, 1.6-meter-wide dark colored granite monument at the seafront
of the Hong Kong Exhibition and Convention Center Extension.
</P>
<P>
The monument bears the seven golden Chinese characters in the
hand-writing of President Jiang Zemin, meaning Monument in
Commemoration of Hong Kong's Return to the Motherland.
</P>
<P>
In his speech at the ceremony, Hu Jintao said that two years
ago, President Jiang Zemin solemnly declared here the resumption
by the Chinese government of the exercise of sovereignty over Hong
Kong and the formal establishment of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region of the People's Republic of China. The
hoisting of the bright five-star red flag and the Hong Kong SAR
flag plunged the entire country into jubilation and attracted
world-wide attention.
</P>
<P>
"Hong Kong has since turned over to a new chapter in its annals,
" he said. "To build a monument in commemoration of this event
will help our future generations to remember this history-making
event and forever carry forward the great patriotic spirit. This
is the shared inspiration of all our compatriots in Hong Kong and
indeed of the Chinese people of all ethnic groups."
</P>
<P>
He said that this monument keeps a historical record of the
struggles waged by sons and daughters of the Chinese nation for
national reunification and territorial integrity; it is a monument
in praise of the great practice of "one country, two systems";
this monument marks the beginning of Hong Kong people acting as
masters of their own and erecting a new milestone in building up
Hong Kong; it is a monument to the important contribution by the
Chinese people to the cause of peace and progress of mankind; and
it is an immortal monument that will stand in the heart of every
Chinese people. It will forever serve as a comfort to the dead, an
encouragement to the people today and an inspiration to the future
generations.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990701.0232 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hu Jintao Attends Monument Unveiling Ceremony in HK (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Over this period, he added, the Hong Kong compatriots have
shared the common fate with the motherland, making significant
contributions to the development of the mainland. With the
constant advancement of China's modernization drive, there will be
closer and more extensive economic links between Hong Kong and the
mainland. Hong Kong will surely continue to play an irreplaceable
critical role in turning China into a strong and prosperous
country. On the other hand, the sustained and steady economic
growth of the mainland will provide a stronger support for Hong
Kong's prosperity.
</P>
<P>
Hu stressed that the central people's government is determined
to implement in full the policy of "one country, two systems", "
Hong Kong people governing Hong Kong", and a high degree of
autonomy as well as the Basic Law. It will never waver in
supporting the SAR government led by Tung Chee Hwa in governing
Hong Kong in accordance with law. "No matter what happens, the
great socialist country will be a strong backing for the continued
prosperity and stability of Hong Kong," he stated.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the conviction that with the correct guidance of
the policy of "one country, two systems", with the industry and
wisdom of the over six million Hong Kong compatriots, with the
effective work of the SAR government led by Tung Chee Hwa and with
the strong support of the people of all ethnic groups and the
central people's government, Hong Kong will overcome all
difficulties on its way ahead, march into the new century with a
fresh new look and bring about new glory.
</P>
