<HEADLINE> Hu Jintao Attends Monument Unveiling Ceremony in HK (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
At the unveiling ceremony, Tung presented to Hu a model of the
monument.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the ceremony, Hu met with the staff members of the
working group in charge of the erection of the monument.
</P>
<P>
The monument is composed of three parts -- the pedestal, the
pillar and the head. It is made up of 206 overlapping stone slabs.
</P>
<P>
A glass ring with built-in lighting marks Hong Kong's return to
China in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The monument is illuminated on four sides by spotlights. At the
top of the head, spotlights pointing to the sky are installed at
the central part to symbolize that Hong Kong will flourish for
ever.
</P>
<P>
Among those present at the unveiling ceremony were Fok Ying-
tung, vice-chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference; Liao Hui, director of
the Hong Kong and Macao Affairs Office of the State Council; Chen
Fujin, deputy director of the General Office of the Central
Committee of the Communist Party of China; Jiang Enzhu, director
of the Xinhua News Agency Hong Kong Branch; Ma Yuzhen,
commissioner of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs in the HKSAR; and
Xiong Ziren and Wang Yufa, commander and political commissar of
the Chinese People's Liberation Army Forces in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The SAR government officials joined more than 1,000 people from
all walks of life at the ceremony. Among them were Andrew Li,
chief justice of the Court of Final Appeal; Anson Chan,
administrative secretary; Rafael Hui Si-yan, acting financial
secretary; Elsie Leung Oi-sie, secretary for Justice; Leung Chun-
ying, convenor of the Executive Council; and Rita Fan, president
of the Legislative Council. 
</P>
