<HEADLINE> Brazil Sets Inflation Targets for 3 Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Brazil has set its inflation
target at eight percent for 1999, Finance Minister Pedro Malan
said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The target for 2000 is six percent and for 2001, four percent,
based on a broad consumer price index.
</P>
<P>
Malan noted that there is a two percentage point margin of
leeway on these inflation targets.
</P>
<P>
Under the new policy, the Central Bank of Brazil will produce
quarterly reports on the country's inflation situation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
