<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Ministers, MPs Banned From Traveling Abroad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan President Chandrika
Kumaratunga has banned cabinet ministers and parliamentarians from
foreign traveling till December 31, reports said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The president said that any minister or parliamentarian who
needs to go abroad for official purposes should obtain her special
consent, the Sinhalese Island newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
Kumaratunga is reported to have made this announcement at a
cabinet meeting held Wednesday at her official residence "Temple
Trees".
</P>
<P>
While no official reason has been given for this decision,
informed sources said that the government is likely to put forward
national elections due in August and November next year.
</P>
<P>
At an executive committee meeting of the Sri Lanka Freedom
Party, the ruling coalition's major partner, it was decided that
preliminary preparations for the elections be made at district
level and accordingly 17 ministers were selected to be the leaders
of these district organizations. 
</P>
