<HEADLINE> Spanish PM Urges IMF to Aid Ecuador </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Spanish Prime Minister Jose
Maria Aznar said here Wednesday that he had called on the
International Monetary Fund (IMF) President Michel Camdessus to
help Ecuador settle its foreign debt.
</P>
<P>
At a joint press conference held with his Ecuadorian
counterpart Jamil Mahuad, Aznar said that world organizations such
as the IMF, the World Bank and the Inter-American Development Bank
should help Ecuador tide over the crisis.
</P>
<P>
He said that during the June 28-29 Rio Summit, the leaders of
all the participating countries expressed support to the
Ecuadorian program.
</P>
<P>
He also noted that the European Union financial ministers
agreed in Cologne, Germany, in early June to cancel 30 percent of
the foreign debt of the countries which are in most critical
situations.
</P>
<P>
Aznar and Mahuad signed a series of agreements ahead of the
press conference, under which Spain will provide more help to the
Latin American country.
</P>
<P>
Ecuador's foreign debt reached to 16 billion U.S. dollars due
to financial crisis and the bad weather caused by El Nino.
</P>
