<HEADLINE> Grizzlies Tab Francis with Second Pick in NBA Draft </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The Vancouver Grizzlies
selected Steve Francis with the second pick in the NBA draft here
tonight, opting for a guard instead of a more-needed frontcourt
player.
</P>
<P>
The Grizzlies appeared set at point guard after selecting Mike
Bibby second overall last year. Nevertheless they tabbed Francis,
who can play both guard positions, rather than Lamar Odom, a multi-
talented forward.
</P>
<P>
The Francis left Maryland after his junior season, when he
averaged 17.0 points, 4.5 assists and 4.5 rebounds and the Terps
to the regional semifinals of the NCAA Tournament.
</P>
<P>
Lightning-quick and an explosive leaper, Francis played
exclusively at shooting guard last season but does have the
ability to play both backcourt positions. He played point guard in
high school and junior college.
</P>
<P>
The Grizzlies won just eight games this season and entertained
offers for the pick, finding nothing overwhelming. The Miami Heat
wanted the pick to select Odom but offered only forward P.J. Brown
and the 25th overall pick. 
</P>
</TEXT>
