<HEADLINE> Highlights of Major Beijing-Based Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Following are the highlights of
today's major Beijing-based newspapers:
</P>
<P>
"People's Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- The Communist Party of China (CPC) must emphasize its
Marxist political stance linked to socialism with Chinese
characteristics in order to maintain benefits for the people,
China's President Jiang Zemin urged yesterday.
</P>
<P>
As general secretary of the CPC Central Committee, Jiang made
his plea when addressing a forum yesterday marking the 78th
anniversary of the founding of Party.
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji yesterday stressed the importance
of scientific and technological reform by being innovative in
using technology in the agricultural and engineering sectors.
</P>
<P>
Zhu, who also heads the State Leading Group for Promoting
Science, Technology and Education, chaired the 4th meeting of the
group and listened to reports made by related departments on the
drafting of the Program for Developing Agricultural Science and
Technology, the progressing of pilot projects for a nationwide
push on innovation in engineering and the development strategy of
China's high-energy physics sector.
</P>
<P>
 "Xinhua Daily Telegraph"
</P>
<P>
-- The 6th, 7th and 8th volumes of "Mao Zedong Works" have
recently been put out by the People's Publishing House.
</P>
<P>
The three volumes of the late Chinese Communist Party chief
incorporate some 300 articles, which were written after 1949; many
of them were published for the first time.
</P>
<P>
The eight volumes of "Mao Zedong Works" are selected among the
manuscripts, speeches, transcripts of talks of the former Party
leader between 1921 and 1976, and represent another comprehensive
collection after the four-volumed "Selected Works of Mao Zedong".
</P>
<P>
The publication was approved by the Communist Party of China (
CPC) Central Committee and compiled by the Party Literature
Research Center of the CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese Vice-president Hu Jintao said in Hong Kong Wednesday
that it is in the fundamental interests of the six million Hong
Kong people to maintain the special administrative region's
prosperity and stability.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting with leading officials of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region HKSAR at the Government House late Wednesday
afternoon, the vice-president stressed that social stability is
the key to Hong Kong's prosperity and development and that
economic prosperity can ensure long-term stability.
</P>
<P>
"China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- China's chief trade negotiator said yesterday that the
interests of developing countries must be taken into consideration
during the coming WTO negotiations about global trade.
</P>
<P>
Long Yongtu, vice-minister of foreign trade and economic
cooperation, said China hopes the contents and outcomes of the new
round of WTO negotiations, which are scheduled to begin in Seattle,
Washington in December, will facilitate the setting up of fairer
and more open trade system.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks to the trade ministers' meeting of the Asia
Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC), which concluded yesterday in
Auckland of New Zealand.
</P>
<P>
-- China yesterday reiterated that Cambodia's handling of the
Khmer Rouge issue is an internal affair of Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan, during his talks with Cambodian
Foreign Minister Hor Nam Hong, said China is confident that the
Cambodian Government and people can judge and resolve all of their
own internal affairs, including the Khmer Rouge issue,
independently. 
</P>
