<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Determined to Implement "One Country, Two Systems" Policy: Hu </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-President Hu Jintao
said here Thursday that the Chinese government is determined to
implement in full the policy of "one country, two systems," "Hong
Kong people administering Hong Kong," and a high degree of
autonomy as well as the Basic Law.
</P>
<P>
Delivering a speech at a ceremony for the unveiling of the
Monument in Commemoration of Hong Kong's Return to China, Hu said
that the central government "will never waver in supporting the
Special Administrative Region (SAR) government led by Chief
Executive Tung Chee Hwa in governing Hong Kong in accordance with
law."
</P>
<P>
"No matter what happens, the great socialist country will be a
strong backing for the continued prosperity and stability of Hong
Kong," said Hu, who arrived here Tuesday for the unveiling
ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The vice-president commented that the policy of "one country,
two systems" and the Basic Law have been implemented in full over
the past two years.
</P>
<P>
The previous social and economic systems as well as the way of
life in Hong Kong remain unchanged, he said. Hong Kong maintains
its status as a free port and a hub of international finance,
trade and navigation, and keeps its extensive ties with foreign
countries, other regions, and relevant international
organizations.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong residents "enjoy all kinds of rights and freedoms
fully," he added.
</P>
<P>
"Facts have eloquently proved that the policy of 'one country,
two systems' and the Basic Law of the Hong Kong SAR not only
conform to the fundamental interests of Hong Kong, but also serve
the interests of investors from all countries. They are the
fundamental guarantee for the long-term prosperity and stability
of Hong Kong," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
Hu expressed his conviction that Hong Kong will overcome all
difficulties on its way ahead "with the correct guidance of the
policy of "one country, two systems," with the industry and wisdom
of the over six million Hong Kong compatriots, with the effective
work of the SAR government and with the strong support of the
people of all ethnic groups and the central people's government.
</P>
</TEXT>
