<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-President Hails HKSAR Government Efforts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-President Hu Jintao
Thursday praised the government of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR) for successfully handling Hong Kong
affairs.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a ceremony to unveil the Monument in Commemoration
of Hong Kong's Return to China, Hu said that Hong Kong compatriots
have, with an unprecedented sense of being the masters of their
own affairs, actively participated in the management of Hong Kong
affairs.
</P>
<P>
"The Hong Kong SAR government, headed by Chief Executive Tung
Chee Hwa, has handled Hong Kong affairs cautiously, but steadily
and firmly, and responded to various challenges calmly," he said.
</P>
<P>
The SAR government has "succeeded in fencing off the strong
impact of the Asian financial crisis on Hong Kong and in
maintaining the prosperity and stability of Hong Kong," he added.
</P>
<P>
"The firm steps forward our Hong Kong compatriots have taken
under the leadership of the SAR government in overcoming
difficulties and warding off risks have shown to the world that
the SAR government led by Mr. Tung Chee Hwa has the wisdom and
capability to handle complicated situation and the people of Hong
Kong are undoubtedly capable of administering Hong Kong well," he
said.
</P>
<P>
Since the founding of the People's Republic of China 50 years
ago, Hu noted, the Hong Kong compatriots have "shared the common
fate with the motherland."
</P>
<P>
With the constant advancement of China's modernization drive,
he said, there will be closer and more extensive economic links
between Hong Kong and the mainland.
</P>
<P>
"Hong Kong will surely continue to play an irreplaceable
critical role in turning China into a strong and prosperous
country," he said. "The sustained and steady economic growth of
the mainland will provide a strong support for Hong Kong's
prosperity."
</P>
<P>
Hu came to Hong Kong from Shenzhen Tuesday for the unveiling of
the monument. 
</P>
