<HEADLINE> NATO to Stay in Albania Till End of Aid Mission </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, June 30 (Xinhua) -- NATO forces will stay in Albania
till its aid mission ends, a NATO officer said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
NATO forces will continue to help Albania reconstruct roads and
other infrastructure facilities in accordance with the agreement
signed between NATO and Albania, Colonel Volfgang Greven, who
worked at the headquarters of the NATO forces in Albania, was
quoted as saying by the Albanian Telegraphic Agency (ATA).
</P>
<P>
NATO forces are repairing some road segments in Albania,
including one to Rinas Airport and a section on the Durres-Kukes
road, said the officer.
</P>
<P>
NATO forces "on humanitarian mission" began to operate in
Albania about two months ago and the contingent currently embraces
some 7,000 persons from NATO's 19-member countries, the ATA said.
</P>
