<HEADLINE> Cuba to Adopt Euro in Business with Europe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The use of the single European currency will make it easier for
Cuba to conduct international business as the U.S. blockade of the
country discourages the use of the dollar, said Francisco Soberon,
President of the Central Bank of Cuba.
</P>
<P>
Two days ago, Cuban President Fidel Castro said in Rio de
Janeiro at the Latin American, Caribbean and the European Union
Summit, that "the euro will help liberate ourselves from the
privileges and the tyranny of the dollar."
</P>
<P>
The European Union is one of Cuba's main business partners,
which are the most important sources of finance for the island
country. 
