<HEADLINE> Wall Street Stocks Rally Strongly After Rate Rising </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
NEW YORK, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Wall Street stocks rallied
strongly Wednesday after the Federal Reserve announced a
moderate rise in interest rates to prevent inflation from
accelerating.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average closed up 155.45 at
10,970.80. The index gained 262.79 points in the two previous
sessions.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock indicators were also higher. The Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 index rose 21.21 at 1,372.66. The technology heavy
Nasdaq index rose 44.01 at the record closing high of 2,685.12,
surpassing the previous high of 2,652.05 set April 26.
</P>
<P>
Investors got relieved after the Federal Reserve announced
the expected increase in interest rates by a quarter percentage
point. The market was also encouraged as the central bank
policy-makers decided to switch their policy directive from
leading toward an increase in rates to neutral, indicating no
additional increase in rates in the near future.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE composite index rose 10.14 at 648.13 and the
American Stock Exchange index rose 20.45 at 797.93. The Russell
2000 index of smaller companies rose 0.79 at 457.67.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 5-to-3 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with 1,960 up, 1,160 down and 450
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume increased to 1.11 billion shares from 811.59
million in the previous session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
