<HEADLINE> China Bans Imports of Zimbabwean Horses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 1 (Xinhua) -- China has banned imports of horses
and animals in the horse family from Zimbabwe due to an outbreak
of African horse disease in the country in February.
</P>
<P>
China suspended imports of horses and related products from
Zimbabwe on May 10, according to a recent notice released by the
State Administration for the Inspection of Import and Export
Commodities.
</P>
<P>
The notice stipulated that all animals in the horse family and
horse-related products brought into the country by travelers or
sent by mail will be confiscated and destroyed.
</P>
<P>
Quarantine departments will destroy all animals and related
products smuggled into China from Zimbabwe, according to the
notice.  
</P>
