People's Republic of China and the bauhinia flag of the HKSAR were
hoisted amidst the playing of the Chinese national anthem. Five
helicopters, draping with the Chinese national flag and the HKSAR
flag, flew overhead, while firefighting and water police boats
sailed past in the Victoria Harbor.
</P>
<P>
More than 1,000 people from different walks of life witnessed
the event.
</P>
<P>
Among those present were Fok Ying-tung, vice-chairman of the
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference; Liao Hui, director of the Hong Kong and Macao Affairs
Office of the State Council; Chen Fujin, deputy director of the
General Office of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of
China; Jiang Enzhu, director of the Xinhua News Agency Hong Kong
Branch; Ma Yuzhen, commissioner of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs
in the HKSAR; and Xiong Ziren, commander, and Wang Yufa, political
commissar, of the Chinese People's Liberation Army Garrison in
Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Chief Justice of the Court of Final Appeal Andrew Li,
Administrative Secretary Anson Chan, Acting Financial Secretary
Rafael Hui Si-yan, Secretary for Justice Elsie Leung Oi-sie,
Convenor of the Executive Council Leung Chun-ying and President of
the Legislative Council Rita Fan were also present at the flag-
raising ceremony. 
