<HEADLINE> PLA Barracks in Hong Kong Open to Local Residents </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Three barracks of the People's
Liberation Army (PLA) Garrison in the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR) were opened to local residents
Thursday on the occasion of the second anniversary of Hong Kong's
return to China.
</P>
<P>
The event, which is aimed at increasing understanding between
the PLA troops and local residents, drew a large number of people
from all walks of life early in the morning.
</P>
<P>
Visitors are arranged to watch a performance of martial arts
and a display of the facilities and weapons of the troops in the
three barracks for ground, naval and air forces at Stanley,
Stonecutter Island and Shek Kong.
</P>
<P>
The garrison's headquarters delivered a total of 10,000 tickets
to social organizations and citizens last Sunday. As tickets
delivered for May 1 opening of the Stonecutter Island and Shek
Kong barracks remain valid, about 20,000 people are expected to
visit the PLA barracks on this opening day, according to a PLA
officer.
</P>
<P>
The PLA troops came to station in Hong Kong after its return to
China on July 1, 1997. 
