<HEADLINE> China Introduces Popular Science Website </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 1 (Xinhua) -- China's first specialized popular
science website --"China Public Understanding of Science" -- went
online earlier today.
</P>
<P>
A senior official with the Ministry of Science and Technology
said the website features 10 subject areas, including policies and
regulations, the development of scientific research, popular
science bases, the frontiers of science and technology, science
forums and technology.
</P>
<P>
He added related information covers science and daily life, the
history of science, mass media coverage of popular science, famous
scientists and scientific centers for students.
</P>
<P>
Introduction of the website represents an important measure
adopted to disseminate scientific and technological information to
the general public, according to the official.
</P>
<P>
The website -- http.//cpus.gov.cn. -- was established by the
Ministry of Science and Technology.  
</P>
