<HEADLINE> Kipketer Clocks Fastest Men's 800 Meters of Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, June 30 (Xinhua) -- World 800 meters record holder
Wilson Kipketer of Denmark clocked the fastest time of the year
for the distance at the Bislett Games athletics competition in
Oslo, Norway.
</P>
<P>
The Kenyan-born runner, 28, timed one minute 43.11 seconds at
this first leg of the Gold League series held at the Bislett
Stadium.
</P>
<P>
World record holder Heile Gebrselassie of Ethiopia ran the
second fastest 5,000 meters of the season in 12:53.92.
</P>
<P>
The speed of his first two kilometers was so fast that it was
very close to that when he set his world record. But he slowed
down in the remaining part of the race.
</P>
<P>
American Marion Jones, one of the few possible winners of the
one million U.S. dollars jackpot on offer for the Gold League, won
the gold medal for the women's 200 meters in 22.22 seconds.
</P>
