<HEADLINE> Facts and Figures: Trade of China's Five Special Economic Zones </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The following are facts and figures
about the foreign trade of China's five special economic zones (
SEZ) for the first five months this year, provided by the General
Administration of Customs:
</P>
<P>
The Xiamen SEZ reported a total foreign trade turnover of 2.271
billion US dollars, down 10.8 percent from the same period last
year. Exports of the SEZ reached 1.244 billion US dollars, down 14.
9 percent, and imports of the SEZ dropped 5.3 percent to 1.027
billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Shenzhen SEZ reported a foreign trade turnover of 9.027
billion US dollars, up 12.6 percent. Exports of the SEZ was
recorded at 4.549 billion US dollars, down 1.8 percent, and
imports of the SEZ stood at 4.479 billion US dollars, up 32.4
percent.
</P>
<P>
The Zhuhai SEZ reported a total foreign trade turnover of 1.914
billion US dollars, down 7.7 percent. Exports of the SEZ was
recorded at 817.333 million US dollars, down 26.1 percent, and
imports of the SEZ stood at 1.097 billion US dollars, up 13.5
percent.
</P>
<P>
The Shantou SEZ reported a total foreign trade turnover of 1.
051 billion US dollars, down 48.2 percent. Exports of the SEZ
stood at 382.234 million US dollars, down 66.8 percent, and
imports of the SEZ at 668.872 million US dollars, down 23.9
percent.
</P>
<P>
Hainan province SEZ reported a total foreign trade volume of
456.487 million US dollars, down 36.7 percent. Exports of the SEZ
stood at 264.599 million US dollars, down 29.6 percent, and
imports of the SEZ at 191.888 million US dollars, down 44.5
percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
