<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Enter Semifinals of Women's World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
SAN JOSE, June 30 (Xinhua) -- China outplayed their Russian
opponents for a 2-0 victory to advance into the semifinals of the
Women's World Cup soccer tournament here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese team enjoyed a good start in the match, but failed
to grasp any of the scoring chances in the first 30 minutes though
they totally dominated their opponents.
</P>
<P>
The Russian team, which qualified to the quarterfinals as
runners-up of Group C, were no match to their Chinese counterparts.
They adopted a defensive tactics in the first half, playing one
forward in the front and had only one shot in the first 45 minutes.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese team nearly scored at the 24th minute but Jin Yan's
shot was just blocked by the Russian goal-keeper.
</P>
<P>
Five minutes later, Liu Ailing released a 35-meter shot, only to
see the ball flying over the crossbar.
</P>
<P>
The Russian goal-keeper also denied an attempt from Chinese
captain Sun Wen at the 35th minute.
</P>
<P>
But two minutes later, after a Chinese attack caused a mess in
front of the Russian goal, the Russian defenders failed to clear the
ball and Pu Wei collected the loose ball and sent home a 35-meter shot.
</P>
<P>
After lagging 1-0 behind, the Russian team tried to play more
aggressively in the second half, but still could not find a way of
penetrating the Chinese defense line.
</P>
<P>
Russian captain Irina Grigorieva, who was voted best player in
two of Russian team's group matches, found it impossible for her to
organise her team's attacking.
</P>
<P>
For most time of the match, Grigorieva had to do a defensive
work as her team were out-shot by their Chinese counterparts 24-2 in
the match.
</P>
<P>
Jin Yan put China 2-0 ahead at the 56th minute when she tapped
in a rebound after Sun Wen's free-kick hit the post.
</P>
<P>
Sun Wen, who has scored 5 goals in the tournament and has a shot at
the best scorer of the tournament, failed to score a goal by herself
in the match, yet she was still named the best player of the match.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese team will play Norway in the semifinals at Boston on
July 4. Norway beat Sweden 3-1 in another quarterfinal match here
on Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
