the first quarter of this year compared with the same period last
year, the worst since the 1984 crisis.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish government will have to promise International
Monetary Fund to limit personnel and investment to public
institutions, less financial supports to agriculture, new
consumption taxes and raise the age limit on retirement.
</P>
<P>
Hurriyet (Freedom):
</P>
<P>
-- The Western countries united against the death penalty
given to Abdullah Ocalan, leader of the outlawed Kurdish Workers'
Party.
</P>
<P>
However, Turkish Foreign Ministry will brief the EU countries
on the preparations of the Turkish Justice Ministry to amend
Turkish Penal Code. 
