<HEADLINE> Facts and Figures: China's Trade With Major L.A. Partners </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The following are facts and figures
on China's trade with major partners in Latin America for the
first five months this year, provided by the General
Administration of Customs:
</P>
<P>
Total trade volume with Brazil reached 595.464 million US
dollars, down 8 percent from the same period last year. China's
exports to Brazil stood at 290.133 million US dollars, down 23.8
percent. Imports from Brazil hit 305.331 million US dollars, up 14.
4 percent.
</P>
<P>
Total trade volume with Chile topped 419.461 million US dollars,
down 9.9 percent. China's exports to Chile declined 13.8 percent
to 212.192 million US dollars, while its imports from Chile
dropped 5.5 percent to 207.269 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Total trade volume with Panama plummeted 31.4 percent to 326.
508 million US dollars, with China's exports to Panama at 325.533
million US dollars, down 31.6 percent, and imports from Panama
rose 126.3 percent to 976,000 US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Total trade volume with Mexico reached 295.176 million US
dollars, down 2.4 percent. While China's exports to Mexico reached
238.832 million US dollars, up 0.8 percent, China's imports from
Mexico declined 13.8 percent to 56.344 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Total trade volume with Argentina declined 16.9 percent to 273.
374 million US dollars. While China's exports to Argentina
plummeted 16.7 percent to 148.984 million US dollars, China's
imports from Argentina dropped 17.2 percent to 124.390 million US
dollars.  
