<HEADLINE> Facts and Figures: Foreign Trade of China's Major Bonded Zones </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The following are facts and figures
about the foreign trade of China's major bonded zones (BZ) between
January and May this year, provided by the General Administration
of Customs:
</P>
<P>
The Tianjin Port BZ reported a total trade volume of 313.461
million US dollars, up 22 percent from the same period last year.
Its exports reached 105.264 million US dollars, up 10.1 percent,
and imports reached 208.197 million US dollars, up 30.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Waigaoqiao BZ reported a foreign trade turnover of
1.628 billion US dollars, up 74.6 percent. Its exports surged 104.
3 percent to 585.112 million, while imports grew 61.4 percent to 1.
043 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Futian Shatoujiao BZ of Shenzhen city, south China's
Guangdong Province, reported a foreign trade volume of 1.083
billion US dollars, up 15.9 percent. Its exports was recorded at
533.651 million US dollars, up 22.4 percent. Its imports climbed
10.2 percent to 549.697 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Beilun Port BZ of Ningbo city, east China's Zhejiang
Province, reported a foreign trade turnover of 186.644 million US
dollars, down 19.6 percent. While exports of the BZ climbed 19.3
percent to 97.371 million, imports plummeted 40.7 percent to 89.
273 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Dayaowan BZ of Dalian city, northeast China's Liaoning
Province, reported a foreign trade turnover of 145.506 million US
dollars, down 6.2 percent. The BZ's exports dropped 4.3 percent to
76.368 million and imports declined 8.2 percent to 69.137 million
US dollars. 
</P>
