<HEADLINE> SIMEX Sets New Trading Record in June </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The Singapore International
Monetary Exchange (SIMEX) Thursday announced that its trading
volume for the month of June 1999 hit an all-time high of
3,243,192 contracts, up 12.9 percent from the 2,873,544 contracts
in June 1998.
</P>
<P>
It also said this was the second time that the exchange's
monthly trading volume had exceeded 3 million contracts after the
previous record of 3,180,314 contracts in September 1998.
</P>
<P>
June also saw SIMEX's highest average daily volume as 147,419
contracts were transacted per day in the month, exceeding the
previous record of 147,072 contracts recorded in September 1998,
it added.
</P>
<P>
In addition, SIMEX announced that a number of individual
products also set new trading records in June.
</P>
<P>
Euro-yen (Tibor--Tokyo inter-bank offered rate) futures chalked
up an all-time-high daily volume of 168,512 on June 30 and the
MSCI (Morgan Stanley Capital International) Taiwan Stock Index
futures contract put up a sterling performance which set records
in daily volume, monthly volume and open interest.
</P>
<P>
The MSCI Singapore Stock Index futures broke the daily volume
record as they traded 3,346 contracts on June 25, just a month
after setting its previous record of 3,339 contracts on May 26.
</P>
</TEXT>
