<HEADLINE> FIFA Selects 50 Finalists for World Cup All-Star Squ ad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
SAN JOSE, June 30 (Xinhua) -- FIFA has selected 50 finalists for
the 3rd women's World Cup soccer tournament all-star Squad.
</P>
<P>
Based on players' performance through the group competitions of
the World Cup, the FIFA Technical Study Group selected a total of 50
players as finalists for the all-star Squad, the first-ever all-star
team selected at a FIFA women's World Cup tournament.
</P>
<P>
Following the quarterfinal matches, the FIFA Technical Study
Group will narrow the list to three players per position, which will
be announced during the semifinal matches. The final selection of
the all-star team, which will include a total of 16 players, will be
made by the FIFA Technical Study Group following the semifinal
matches and announced at Los Angeles on July 8. 
</P>
