Northern Ireland is facing the moment of truth as British Prime
Minister Tony Blair and his Irish counterpart Bertie Ahern tried
to arrange a compromise by midnight Wednesday between Catholics
and Protestants on the application of the peace agreement, in
particular the disarmament of militia forces of the two
belligerent sides.
</P>
<P>
