<HEADLINE> Nigeria Makes Agriculture Number One Priority </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Nigerian President OLusegun Obasanjo
has said that his government would give top priority to
agriculture, The Post Express reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted the president as saying on Wednesday that
"agriculture is our number one priority because of many reasons."
</P>
<P>
President Obasanjo pointed out that the issue of agriculture
had transcended beyond family lines, "it is now a matter of
national security."
</P>
<P>
In keeping the tempo of agriculture at the level of sustainable
 development, the president promised to subsidize fertilizer.
Such subsidy would be cautiously pursued, a departure from the
indiscriminate manner of the previous governments, he said.
</P>
<P>
"I will make sure that the subsidy benefits get to the
farmers," President Obasanjo assured.
</P>
<P>
At a press briefing on Tuesday in capital Abuja, Nasarawa State
Governor Alhaji Abdullahi Adamu said the Nigerian government had
decided to subsize the price of fertilizer by 25 percent as part
of efforts to revitalize the agriculture sector in the country.
</P>
<P>
He said that the decision was part of the resolutions of the
inaugural meeting of the Council of State presided over by
President Obasajo on Tuesday in Abuja.
</P>
<P>
The governor noted that arrangements had also bee made to
ensure that fertilizer get to farmers as soon possible. 
</P>
