<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Spokesman on EU's New Decision on China's Wooden Crates (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The European Union's new decision
to delay the date to implement its new quarantine standard imposed
on Chinese wooden crates, boxes and pallets used for exporting
goods until July 10 will help reduce the losses of the Chinese
side, a spokesman of the Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation (MOFTEC) said here today.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman Hu Chusheng said that China has noted the EU's new
decision, which extends the grace period by a month, and considers
it will reduce the expected losses for owners of the wooden crated
goods waiting for shipment at Chinese ports.
</P>
<P>
China's foreign trade companies, meanwhile, are making vigorous
efforts to pack their goods according to the new quarantine
standard of the EU side, Hu said, aiming to cut the negative
impact of the EU's decision on China's exports to the minimum.
</P>
<P>
China strongly resented the EU's decision targeting wood-crates
used for Chinese exports to Europe, because it could "adversely
affect Chinese exports valued at some seven billion U.S. dollars,"
Hu announced earlier last month after the EU's decision was
announced on June 1.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990701.0399 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Meets Cambodian Foreign Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji said
today that China and Cambodia should reinforce bilateral
cooperation in various fields to bring traditional Sino-Cambodian
friendship up to a new level.
</P>
<P>
The Premier made the statement during a meeting here this
afternoon with Hor Nam Hong, Cambodia's senior minister and
minister of foreign affairs and international cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said that China and Cambodia, both developing countries,
have no problems left over from history nor current conflicts in
their interests, and it is the common aspiration of the two sides
to intensify bilateral cooperation.
</P>
<P>
China values its economic and trade ties with Cambodia on the
basis of equality and mutual benefit and it is willing to provide
support and help to the economic reconstruction in Cambodia within
China's ability, Zhu told Hor Nam Hong.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that China is pleased to see that the
Cambodia's new government, under the leadership of King Sihanouk,
has scored fresh progress in its internal and foreign affairs. "We
believe that the new government of Cambodia will grasp the
historic opportunity to put forward the process of national
reconciliation and make even greater achievements in national
construction", Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
Hor Nam Hong said that Cambodia-China relations have witnessed
a good momentum of development since Cambodian Prime Minister Hun
Sen's successful visit to China last February. He told Zhu that
the related government departments of Cambodia are working to
implement the common ground reached by the leaders of the two
countries to promote bilateral cooperative ties.
</P>
<P>
Hor Nam Hong also briefed Zhu on the domestic situation in
Cambodia and voiced the hope that more Chinese enterprises would
invest in his country.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
