<DOCNO> XIE19990701.0401 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Spokesman on EU's New Decision on China's Wooden Crates (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The EU's June 1 announcement urged member nations to adopt
immediate measures to implement new inspection standards for
packaging using wooden crates or materials for exports from China
after June 10.
</P>
<P>
Gao Hucheng, MOFTEC assistant minister, met with the European
Union Ambassador to China Endymion Wilkinson on June 11 to lodge a
serious complaint about the EU's decision, saying that China
reserves the right to take further actions.
</P>
<P>
But, MOFTEC officials told Xinhua on June 18 that Chinese
export companies have been told to improve the quality and
standard when using wooden boxes for packing their export products
in a special notice issued by MOFTEC and several other Chinese
ministerial departments.
</P>
<P>
Export companies have been warned to carefully select wooden
boxes, crates and pallets according to the new required standards.
Below standard wood must be specially treated before being used as
packaging for exports.
</P>
<P>
"We hope that the EU side will, in accordance with the spirit
of bilateral agreement on trade and economic cooperation, enhance
negotiations and avoid unilateral trade restriction measures that
will affect adversely the normal growth of bilateral trade," Hu
said today.
</P>
<P>
In addition, he said that China also hopes that the EU and its
member nations would reduce arbitrary actions in carrying out
relevant regulations so as to maintain normal development of
bilateral trade relations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
