<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe's Vice-President Dies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In 1963, Ukomo founded the Zimbabwe African People's Union
(ZAPU), and later fled to Zambia and led guerrilla units to wage a
people's war against the British-fostered regime in the country
while Robert Mugabe led the Zimbabwe African National Union
(ZANU), using Mozambique as a base to fight from the east.
</P>
<P>
From 1976 on, the two factions joined efforts in fighting in
the name of the Patriotic Front (PF) against the Ian Smith regime
in the country. And on April 18 1980, Zimbabwe became independent.
</P>
<P>
On December 22, 1987, Nkomo and Mugabe signed the historic
Unity Accord between Zapu (PF) and (PF) .
</P>
<P>
On August 8,1990, Nkomo was sworn in as co-vice president of
Zimbabwe, together with Simon Muzenda -- a post he held till his
death. 
