<HEADLINE> Chinese Twins Become Recipients Of China's Largest Life Insurance Settlement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Two boys in Beijing have become the
beneficiaries of China's largest life insurance payment, it was
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The twins were paid 120,000 yuan by the Kangtai Life Insurance
Company as an annual payment, the remaining 1.92 million yuan of
which will be paid out over the next 13 years, as the result of
their father's life insurance policy.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, he bought of several types of insurance covering the
two boys' schooling, his own life, medical expenses, and
hospitalization, and when he died a year later of malignant cancer
the insurance company, which had got involved as soon as he was
hospitalized, had to pay.
</P>
<P>
Life insurance is still something new to most Chinese,
especially those in the countryside. The majority of life
insurance buyers are in large and economically developed cities
like Beijing, Shanghai, Guangzhou and Shenzhen. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
