<HEADLINE> China Issuing 5th Version of Renminbi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 1 (Xinhua) -- China's State Council announced
today that the 5th version of the Renminbi, the country's currency,
will be issued to meet the country's economic development needs,
improve China's monetary system and increase the ability to stop
counterfeiters.
</P>
<P>
Premier Zhu Rongji has signed a decree saying the People's Bank
of China, the nation's central bank, will begin issuing the new
bills on October 1. They come in 100-yuan, 50-yuan, 20-yuan, 10-
yuan, 5-yuan, 1-yuan, 5-jiao (one-tenth of a yuan), and 10-jiao
notes. The specific date of issue for most of the notes has not
been announced, but the central bank said that the 100-yuan note
will be issued on October 1.
</P>
<P>
The new 100-yuan note, whose main color is red, carries a
picture of a bust of the late Chairman Mao Zedong on the obverse
side and Beijing's Great Hall of the People on the reverse side.
</P>
<P>
The premier's decree says that neither units nor individuals
can refuse to accept any of the new notes for any reason.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
