<DOCNO> XIE19990701.0442 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Body Calls for Aid Suspension to Somali Gedo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The Somalia Aid Coordination Body
Thursday recommended the suspension of all kinds of aid to Gedo
region in southern Somalia due to the murder of an Italian aid
worker in January this year.
</P>
<P>
On January 26, Dr. Singh Bohgal, a veterinarian who was working
with Terra Nuova, an Italian non-governmental organization, was
murdered in Gedo region, and punishment has been delayed to impose
on the perpetrators.
</P>
<P>
In a release issued here, the Somali Aid Coordination Body, an
agency comprising donors, U.N. agencies and international
non-governmental organizations, said the murder was "an outrageous
crime and a provocative act totally contrary to the Code of
Conduct for International Relief and Development Assistance to
Somalia."
</P>
<P>
The coordination body requested that local authorities must
apprehend and punish the perpetrators of this crime and recover
the money and equipment stolen from the organization and return to
the Terra Nuova.
</P>
<P>
In March, representatives of the Executive Committee of the
coordination body visited the area and met with local authorities,
and agreed upon a given period of eight weeks for local
authorities to punish the perpetrators and to retrieve the stolen
equipment and money.
</P>
<P>
The coordination body noted that to date, "twelve weeks have
passed and no action has been taken" by local authorities, and
thus it recommended the immediate suspension of all rehabilitation
and development assistance to the region.
</P>
<P>
The body held local Somali authorities and communities
responsible for guaranteeing that secure conditions prevail for
aid agencies and their staff. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
