<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Malaysia Registers Trade Surplus of 1.68 Bln Dollars in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, July 1 (Xinhua) -- A much faster growth in
exports than in imports helped Malaysia to chalk up a trade
surplus of 6.4 billion ringgit (1.68 billion U.S. dollars) in May
compared with a smaller surplus of 3.8 billion ringgit (one
billion dollars) a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
This is the 19th consecutive month since November 1997 that
Malaysia recorded a surplus, the Statistics Department said when
releasing preliminary external trade figures Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Exports rose 14.7 percent in May while imports increased 3.2
percent, the department said.
</P>
<P>
As for the first five months of this year, the surplus rose 74
percent to 28.2 billion ringgit (7.42 billion dollars) from 16.3
billion ringgit (4.29 billion dollars) recorded in the same period
last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
