<HEADLINE> Chinese Official Disciplined Because of Massage Parlor Behavior </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, July 1 (Xinhua) -- An official in Yinchuan, capital
of the Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region in northwest China, was given
strict sanctions by the city's disciplinary department after
having been caught scuffling with a masseuse after having enjoyed
her services in the nude.
</P>
<P>
Xing Wenbin, director of the municipal social security affairs
bureau and a deputy to the municipal people's congress, was caught
in the act by disciplinary officials of the regional government.
</P>
<P>
Xing confessed that he had argued about payment with the girl
after having received a massage in the nude when he visited the
sauna at the invitation of the boss of a local construction
company.
</P>
<P>
He has been removed from his government position and expelled
from the municipal people's congress. As a member of the Communist
Party of China, Xing has also been placed on probation with the
Party.
</P>
<P>
These "pornographic" services are outlawed in China but there
are still people who engage in the risky business because of the
profits.  
</P>
</TEXT>
