<DOCNO> XIE19990701.0453 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nepal to Develop Key Sectors for Poverty Reduction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Nepali King Birendra said
Thursday that in order to meet the principal objective of poverty
alleviation, the government will strive to expand economic
activities in such fields as agriculture, water resources,
tourism, physical infrastructure, industry and commerce.
</P>
<P>
Outlining the government's policies and programs for the
1999/2000 fiscal year starting mid-July, King Birendra said that
various policies and programs will be implemented to increase the
people's earning, raise employment, eliminate discrimination and
inequality prevailing in the economic and social life of the
country.
</P>
<P>
He told parliament that as a large majority of the people
depend on agriculture for livelihood, the government will adopt
policies to commercialize agriculture, establish agro-based
industries, develop rural infrastructures and promote tourism and
small and cottage industries.
</P>
<P>
He said time-bound programs will be implemented to solve the
problems of the landless people and bonded labor prevailing in the
country, one of the poorest in the world.
</P>
<P>
The king said policies will also be adopted to expand such
infrastructures as education, health care, communications,
transportation and electricity for a balanced development of the
country with special priority given to the mountainous and
backward districts.
</P>
<P>
"Guided by the motto of 'development of water resources: key to
national prosperity,' my government will formulate a national
strategy for the overall development of this sector based on
national consensus," he said.
</P>
<P>
Nepal boasts a hydropower potential of 83,000 MW but only 257
MW have been exploited.
</P>
<P>
"A bill will be presented before the parliament for timely
improvements in the existing policies and laws so as to attract
internal as well as external private investment for the
development of hydro-power projects," King Birendra said.
</P>
<P>
He pledged that the government will make the economic system
even more attractive, liberal and competitive by way of additional
policy reforms and improvements in legal, administrative and
procedural matters to instill further dynamism in the industry and
commerce sectors and attract local and foreign investment.
</P>
<P>
"With a view to developing a self-reliant economy and gradually
reducing foreign aid dependence, my government will lay emphasis
on the productive utilization of foreign aid," he said.
</P>
<P>
"Special emphasis will be given to managing expenditures,
mobilizing revenue and financial discipline," he added.
</P>
<P>
The Nepali Congress government, which was formed in May after
the general elections, is the first majority government in Nepal
in four and a half years.
</P>
<P>
The emergence of a hung parliament in the mid-term polls in
November 1994 had resulted in political instability, which had
seriously hurt the country's development. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
