<HEADLINE> Chinese Art Exhibition Opens in Dhaka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 1 (Xinhua) -- A 10-day Chinese Art Exhibition
featuring oil paintings and engravings opened at the Bangladesh
Shilpakala Academy in the Bangladeshi capital on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition comprises 59 works of oil painting and graphic
engraving by 54 contemporary artists of China, who use different
media and techniques to express their deep love of nature and sing
the praises of life.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition would mark a major departure from the
traditional watercolors mostly displayed by Chinese painters the
world over, according to Qiu Baiping, a professor of the China
Central Academy of Arts and Design, who was here to represent the
art exhibition.
</P>
<P>
The show would allow Bangladeshi viewers a more contemporary
insight into the works of oil painting and engraving in China, he
said. Two of Qiu' recent works were displayed at the exhibition.
</P>
<P>
Qiu will host a five-day workshop during his stay in
Bangladesh, to train 15 students of the Institute of Fine Arts,
Dhaka on watercolors. 
</P>
