<HEADLINE> Pakistan PM's China Visit Successful: Foreign Secretary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's Foreign Secretary
Shamshad Ahmad said Thursday that Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif's
visit to China was successful and the Pakistani side is fully
satisfied with it.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the media, Shamshad said the discussions
held by Sharif with the Chinese leaders were "positive and
substantive," focusing not only on further enhancing the
multi-dimensional cooperation between the two countries but also
on the current volatile situation in the region.
</P>
<P>
"The talks were reflective of the warmth and sincerity of the
abiding friendship between Pakistan and China," he said.
</P>
<P>
The discussions, he added, enabled the two sides to take stock
of all aspects of the current situation and its inextricable links
with the larger issue of Kashmir which lies at the heart of the
tension in the region.
</P>
<P>
Both sides agreed that a final settlement of this core issue
would bring about a durable peace in the region, Shamshad added.
</P>
<P>
"Talks were very productive and we are fully satisfied," he
said.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that other major powers will adopt an
approach which helps promote peace rather than complicate the
situation.
</P>
<P>
Shamshad also hoped that in view of the serious situation in
Kashmir, the world's major powers will use their influence with
India to join Pakistan in bringing to an end the present crisis in
Kargil and beginning a meaningful process for resolving the core
issue of Kashmir. 
</P>
