<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Guard Carlton Myers contributed 22
points and forward Gregor Fucka added 19 as Italy beat Russia 102-
79 to reach the semi-finals of the European Championship on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
That also meant Italy has qualified for next year's Olympics in
Sydney.
</P>
<P>
Italy, silver medalists at the Europeans two years ago,
overwhelmed Russia with its well-organized defense and good
outside shooting.
</P>
<P>
Myers sparked an Italian burst with 15 minutes remaining on the
clock, hitting two 3-pointers for an 11-point lead. Myers made
four of his five 3-point attempts.
</P>
<P>
Successive 3-pointers by Fucka and Alessandro Abbio made it an
18-point game with just over four minutes left on the clock and
the Italians went to their bench to finish the game.
</P>
<P>
Italy next faces the winner of the Yugoslavia-Germany
quarterfinal. 
