<HEADLINE> Barak to Meet Arafat Soon After Forming Government </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Israeli Prime Minister-elect Ehud
Barak said on Thursday he is going to meet with Palestinian leader
Yasser Arafat as soon as he finishes the formation of a new
government.
</P>
<P>
In a telephone conversation with Arafat, Barak also briefed
Arafat on the progress of his efforts in grouping a broad-based
coalition government, an announcement of Barak's Labor party said.
</P>
