receiving criticism from Arafat, who reportedly complained that
Barak has not contacted him after winning the May 17 prime
ministerial election in Israel.
</P>
<P>
Barak is scheduled to visit the United States in mid-July and
the White House has requested Barak to meet with Arafat before
going to Washington.
</P>
<P>
Barak will submit his cabinet list to the Knesset (parliament)
next Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
He has promised to start negotiations with Syria, Lebanon and
the Palestinians soon after his government assumes the office.
</P>
