<HEADLINE> German Ship Outfitters Warned of Tough Asian Competition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, July 1 (Xinhua) -- German officials warned on Thursday
that a low-price offensive by Asian shipyards is posing a tough
challenge to German shipping industry suppliers which promises to
last a long time, the Deutsche Press Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The German Shipbuilding and Offshore Supply Industry
Association in Hamburg said that more and more orders are going to
South Korea, Japan and China and that German firms are facing a
lasting and difficult stretch of low-price competition against the
Asians.
</P>
<P>
The association said the response of German maritime equipment
suppliers would be to go where the customers are and establish a
strong local presence in Asia.
</P>
<P>
With an annual turnover of around 8.5 billion U.S. dollars and
a work force of 70,000, Germany's shipbuilding suppliers industry
is larger than the shipbuilding sector itself. 
</P>
