<HEADLINE> India Declares Recapture of Key Positions in Kashmir </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 30 (Xinhua) -- India said on Wednesday that its
troops had recaptured four key positions held by "intruders" from
Pakistan in Drass and Batalik sectors of Kashmir, and killed more
than 40 "infiltrators" but lost 26 of its soldiers.
</P>
<P>
An Indian Army spokesman told the press here that mopping-up
operations were still going on.
</P>
<P>
Press reports from Kashmir said that artillery shells fired by
Pakistan hit two schools in an area at Drass near some residential
houses and a local powerhouse.
</P>
<P>
An Indian Air Force spokesman said that in addition to
reconnaissance and other missions, air strikes continued against
selected targets mainly in Drass and Batalik sectors.
</P>
<P>
The army spokesman said that 201 Indian personnel had been
killed and 384 others wounded while nine were missing in action.
</P>
</TEXT>
