<HEADLINE> Newspaper Editorial on Chinese Communist Party Anniversary (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The People's Daily newspaper has
called for the building up of the Party's power and greatness, in
an editorial to be published on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The editorial stresses that the speech made by Communist Party
of China (CPC) Central Committee General Secretary and Chinese
President Jiang Zemin at a forum on June 28 marking the 78th
anniversary of the founding of the CPC is a guideline for thus
building up the Party in these new, exciting and interesting times.
</P>
<P>
It says that Jiang's speech is highly instructive for both
improving the Party and pushing forward the reform, opening up and
modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
Jiang emphasized in his speech that an extensive education
drive in theoretical study, political awareness and expecting good
conduct among government officials above the county level is a
prevailing priority of the Party at present.
</P>
<P>
The editorial sums up in one dynamic sentence the long and
glorious, if somewhat tortuous, history of the CPC as it drove
forward the revolutionary and construction course of the country:
"The key lies in the Party." It insists that without the CPC,
there would never have been a new China, the growth of socialism,
the great achievements of the reform, opening up and modernization
drive, or the bright prospects now facing the country and the
people.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
