<HEADLINE> Strengthening Work on Ethnic Affairs : Party Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"The Party's work on ethnic affairs should only be strengthened,
not weakened," said Wei here today at a forum marking the
publication of the "Selected Works of Ulanhu" with an inscription
of President Jiang Zemin.
</P>
<P>
The forum was jointly held by the United Front Work Department
of the CPC and the regional CPC committee of Inner Mongolia
Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
To do a good job in ethnic affairs, Wei said, we should first
correctly handle the relationship between the central authorities
and the autonomous regions. "On the other hand, measures should
also be taken to accelerate both social and economic development
of areas mainly populated by minority Chinese," he said.
</P>
<P>
Wei also pointed to the importance of safeguarding unity among
all ethnic groups in China and urged officials in the autonomous
regions to creatively implement the policy of the Party on the
work of ethnic affairs.
</P>
<P>
He praised Ulanhu for his creativity in solving problems
related to China's minority ethnic groups.
</P>
<P>
Ulanhu (1906-1988), formerly the Vice-president of the People's
Republic of China, was a native of the Inner Mongolia Autonomous
Region. He joined the Communist Youth League of China (CYLC) in
December 1923 and became a member of the Communist Party of China
(CPC) in September 1925.
</P>
<P>
Also present at today's forum were Ulanhu's son, Buhe, vice-
chairman of the Standing Committee of the National People's
Congress, Wang Zhaoguo vice-chairman of the Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) National Committee, and
other senior CPC leaders.
</P>
<P>
The "Selected Works of Ulanhu" include articles, notes,
speeches, and talks written or made between 1945 and 1988.
</P>
</TEXT>
