<HEADLINE> Newspaper Editorial on Chinese Communist Party Anniversary (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The editorial points out that the CPC has overcome many
difficulties and paid certain prices for every step forward it has
made in the past 78 years. Its future depends on the quality and
standards it imposes and on its insight and mastering of the
situation both in China and in the world.
</P>
<P>
"The 78 years of history have proved that our Party is the only
Party that insists on combining the basic principles of Marxism
with China's real conditions and characteristics while
continuously pushing forward historic progress and acting as a
trail blazer," the editorial says.
</P>
<P>
It praises the CPC for faithfully serving the Chinese people
and bringing about big and beneficial changes in the country; for
withstanding setbacks and severe tests of its courage and
fortitude while also maintaining vitality by being at the
forefront of historical trends.
</P>
<P>
These new times, new situations and tasks have imposed higher
and more stringent requirements on the Party in terms of the arts
of leadership and government, along with the quality and
capability of its leadership at all levels, the editorial says.
</P>
<P>
On the present situation, it points out that the reform and
opening up course of action has encountered some deep-rooted
problems, about which we know little of the rules on how to tackle
them, as yet.
</P>
<P>
The polarization of world politics and globalization of the
world economy pose both opportunities and grim challenges for a
China that is rapidly, with big strides, closing up on the rest of
the world.
</P>
<P>
The hegemony and power politics adopted by certain Western
powers make China fully aware that the world is not yet a peaceful
one and that hostile forces in the West will not give up attempts
to try and bring about China's fall, the editorial says.
</P>
