<DOCNO> XIE19990701.0508 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Congolese Rebels Threaten to Boycott Lusaka Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Congolese rebels have threatened
to withdraw from the Lusaka peace negotiations if ousted leader
Ernest Wamba dia Wamba is given a seat as a rebel representative,
the Rwanda News Agency reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Vice-President of the Congolese Rally for Democracy (CRD),
Moise Nyarugabo, was quoted as saying that the CRD has formed a
common front with another rebel group, the Congolese Liberation
Movement led by Jean Pierre Bemba.
</P>
<P>
"There is no room for ousted Wamba," Nyarugabo said. "We cannot
 accept to be imposed representatives in the Lusaka talks."
</P>
<P>
According to the rebel leader, the talks in Zambian capital
Lusaka hit a snag Tuesday with Zimbabwe and the Democratic
Republic of Congo (DRC) insisted in integrating Wamba in the rebel
delegation.
</P>
<P>
"This is unacceptable that (Zimbabwean President) Robert Mugabe
 and (DRC President) Laurent Kabila appoint our representative to
the talks,'' Nyarugabo said.
</P>
<P>
"We will pull out of talks if this situation prevails with
Kabila and allies making every thing they can to cripple progress
in the talks," the rebel leader added. 
</P>
