<HEADLINE> French PM to Visit Russia This Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 30 (Xinhua) -- French Prime Minister Lionel Jospin
will pay an official visit to Russia from Thursday to Friday this
week, his second visit to Moscow in two years, announced the
French government on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Jospin will preside with his Russian counterpart Serguey
Stepashine the fifth session of Franco-Russian mixed commission of
government ministers.
</P>
<P>
He will focus his talks with Russian leaders on Russia's
economic problems, the country's economic reform, and the
establishment of fiscal and other regulations by Russia to draw
foreign investment.
</P>
<P>
Jospin and Russian leaders will also discuss bilateral trade
and cooperation in the fields of airspace, telecommunications,
energy, agriculture and food, said French officials.
</P>
<P>
Bilateral trade volume between France and Russia dropped by 25
percent in 1998 as is compared with 1997, mainly because of the
financial and economic crises in Russia. 
</P>
