<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Official Says Duty-free Benefit For Citizens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELES June 30 (Xinhua) -- European Union (EU) is formally
to abolish duty-free shops in its 15 member states at midnight
Wednesday, saying it is good news for taxpayers.
</P>
<P>
Duty-free sales to travellers will come to an end at midnight
on June 30 in accordance with the unanimous decision of the EU
Council of Finance Ministers adopted in 1991, European Commission
said today in a statement. "This is excellent news for EU
taxpayers," said Mario Monti, European Commissioner for EU
internal market.
</P>
<P>
"It ends the curious situation under which massive subsidies,
worth over two billion euros every year, were paid to air and see
travel within the EU," the commissioner said.
</P>
<P>
Monti also said that many duty-free sales operators have
announced that they will maintain not only retail sales to
travellers but also "their prices on the majority of goods sold by
absorbing from their profit margins the value-added taxes that
will be applicable from tomorrow".
</P>
<P>
"It is a compliment to democracy in the EU that the interests
of a narrow-interest lobby group with seemingly unlimited
financial resources proved unable to overturn a unanimous decision
of EU member states," the EU commissioner said.
</P>
<P>
"Just in case some travellers may have been misinformed or are
unaware, I would like to reemphasize that people's rights
concerning cross-border shopping are not affected by the abolition
of duty free sales within the EU," Monti said, adding people will
still be able to buy goods for their own personal use without
limit in other member states and will not have to pay any
additional taxes or excises when they return home. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
