<HEADLINE> France Warns Against Breakaway of Montenegro from FRY </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 30 (Xinhua) -- France warned on Wednesday against a
possible breakaway of Montenegro from the Federal Republic of
Yugoslavia (FRY), which now consists of Serbia and Montenegro.
</P>
<P>
``France holds to warn against the risks of regional
destabilization which such an attempt could bring about,'' said
French Foreign Ministry spokeswoman Anne Gazeau-Secret.
</P>
<P>
She said that Montenegro's President Milo Djukanovic has never
expressed his intention to secede the republic from FRY.
</P>
<P>
But the spokeswoman also said that France has supported for
years Djukanovic's efforts at ``democratization of institutions
and political life'' of Montenegro.
</P>
<P>
``These efforts, which we continue to support, are carried out
in the framework of FRY,'' she said.
</P>
<P>
The spokeswoman said that France is due to provide Montenegro
with 5.5 million francs (848,000 U.S. dollars) worth of
humanitarian aid to Montenegro, including food and other
agricultural materials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
