Wednesday that the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK)
appears to be making preparations for a new missile launch.
</P>
<P>
Washington is certain to use this as a pretext for strengthening
its military presence in the Asian and Pacific area.
</P>
<P>
"I think it is fair to say that we have seen some
preparations... some indications of a potential launch in the
future," Deputy Assistant Defense Secretary Kurt Campbell told
reporters.
</P>
