missile being prepared for launch or a possible time schedule.
</P>
<P>
He refused to discus details what U.S. intelligence, including
satellites, might have gathered. But he said South Korea's
President Kim Dae-jung, who will hold talks with President Bill
Clinton in Washington on Friday, had spoken sternly against such a
step.
</P>
<P>
"We do not have enough indications yet to know what kind of
system is potentially being contemplated for launch now," he said.
