<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tanzanian President Commends Kabila's Peace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Tanzanian President Benjamin
Mkapa has commended President Laurent Kabila of the Democratic
Republic of Congo (DRC) for his efforts in searching for a
peaceful solution to the conflicts in the vast central African
country.
</P>
<P>
In a message of congratulations to Kabila on DRC's National Day
on June 29, Mkapa reiterated the need to "continue exploring all
avenues to peace and stability in the region and the continent" to
enable people to enjoy the fruits of development.
</P>
<P>
In the message issued by Tanzanian Foreign Ministry Wednesday,
Mkapa also expressed his government's satisfaction with the
"cordial and brotherly" relations between Tanzania and the DRC.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that Tanzania cherished the relations and will
continue to consolidate and promote bilateral ties in various
fields. 
</P>
