<HEADLINE> Bush Raises 35.5 Million Dollars For Presidential </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 30 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Republican front-runner
George W. Bush broke presidential fund-raising records with a
collection of 35.5 million dollars in the first six months of
1999.
</P>
<P>
The fund Bush raised is nearly 10 times as much as his closest
Republican rival and millions more than Vice President Al Gore,
the Democratic front-runner.
</P>
<P>
Gore, who only has one Democratic rival and has the power of the
White House behind him, raised 17 million dollars less than Bush.
</P>
<P>
Bush, at a news conference today in Los Angeles, said his
campaign was still counting donations and termed the figure a
"minimum number" .
</P>
<P>
"I am, as you can imagine, amazed at the outpouring of
support." he said.
</P>
<P>
Gore, who released his totals Tuesday, collected 18.2 million
dollars to 18.5 million dollars in the first six months of the
campaign.
</P>
<P>
His only rival, former New Jersey Senator Bill Bradley, will
report slightly more than 11.5 million dollars in overall
contributions, according to his spokesman Eric Hauser.  
</P>
</TEXT>
