<HEADLINE> Monument Marking Hong Kong's Return to China Unveiled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-President Hu Jintao
and Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa unveiled a monument in
commemoration of Hong Kong's return to China here Thursday
morning.
</P>
<P>
The monument is temporarily erected at the seafront of the Hong
Kong Convention and Exhibition Center Extension where the handover
ceremony was held two years ago.
</P>
<P>
Standing 20 meters high and made up of 206 overlapping stone
slabs, the monument bears the inscription of President Jiang
Zemin.
</P>
<P>
Upon the completion of the proposed new SAR government
headquarters in the Central district on Hong Kong Island, the
monument will be relocated permanently on the open space off the
new headquarters. 
</P>
