<BODY>
<HEADLINE> North Ireland Peace Talks Continue Despite Deadline </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Northern Ireland's peace talks are
continuing despite the passing of the Wednesday midnight "absolute
" deadline set by British Prime Minister Tony Blair, without any
sign of a breakthrough on the issue of guerrilla disarmament which
has paralyzed the province's peace process.
</P>
<P>
North Ireland's main Protestant leader David Trimble, head of
the Ulster Unionist Party (UUP), charged the Irish Republican Army
's political wing Sinn Fein had not offered anything to break the
deadlock.
</P>
<P>
"We have not received any concrete proposals," the Reuters news
agency quoted Trimble as telling reporters an hour before the
deadline expired.
</P>
<P>
Sinn Fein President Gerry Adams made an eleventh hour
impassioned plea to look to the future but insisted there would be
no immediate handover of guerrilla arms. He warned that the peace
talks could collapse unless agreement was reached between the pro-
Irish Sinn Fein and the pro-British Unionists over guerrilla arms
and the setting up of a power-sharing executive for the province.
</P>
<P>
"Prior decommissioning is not achievable," Adams said, "It is
whether we move forward, based on jumping together into the future
or go lurching back into the past."
</P>
<P>
Throughout Wednesday, Blair and Irish Prime Minister Bertie
Ahern, his co-broker at the talks, put pressure on Sinn Fein and
the Unionists to shift ground so they could reach a compromise,
sources close to the talks said.
</P>
<P>
Unionists want Sinn Fein to give a clear guarantee that IRA
arms will be handed over and refuse to share power with the
republicans until this happens, but Sinn Fein says it has no
authority to make pledges on behalf of the IRA.
</P>
<P>
Failure to break the deadlock was widely considered to fuel a
political vacuum at time of tension across the province as the
climax nears of the traditionally volatile Protestant "marching
season" to celebrate historic battlefield victories over Catholics.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990701.0595 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Clippers Select Lamor Odom with Fourth Pick </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The Los Angeles Clippers would
let Lamar Odom drop no further, taking the multi-talented forward
fourth overall in the 1999 NBA draft.
</P>
<P>
Odom has skills that fit four positions but hurt his stock with
a series of inexplicable moves, including failing to show up for
his physical examination and trying to re-enter Rhode Island after
hiring and firing an agent. He could have been the top pick in the
draft.
</P>
<P>
Odom declared for the NBA draft on the last possible day,
forgoing his final two years of eligibility. He is a rare talent,
a player with size who can play on the wing.
</P>
<P>
Odom averaged 17.6 points, 9.4 rebounds and 3.8 assists in his
only collegiate season, leading the Rams to the NCAA Tournament.
He shot 48.2 percent from the field but only 33 percent from 3-
point range and committed nearly as many turnovers as assists.
</P>
<P>
As an NBA player, his flexibility can be used at either
shooting guard or small forward will be his biggest asset.
</P>
</TEXT>
