<HEADLINE> Ukrainian President Stresses Importance of Defense Capability </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Ukrainian President Leonid Kuchma
stressed here Wednesday that one of the priority tasks of Ukraine'
s national policy is to enhance the country's defense capability.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a graduation ceremony at the Ukrainian Defense
Academy, Kuchma, who is also the Commander-in-Chief of the armed
forces of Ukraine, said that one of the priority tasks of Ukraine'
s national policy is to provide material and technological
guarantee for the armed forces, and to create necessary conditions
for enhancing their combat capability and training level.
</P>
<P>
He said that it was also important to raise the social status
of the servicemen and provide for their material well-being,
because the armed forces are the reliable guarantee for stability,
sovereignty and territorial integrity.
</P>
<P>
Ukraine's domestic and foreign policies should serve the
interests of the country and the nation, the president said.
</P>
<P>
Ukraine has been upholding a non-aligned foreign policy since
its independence, and it has been developing and will continue to
develop effective cooperation in technology with CIS countries,
Russia in particular, NATO member nations and other countries, he
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
