<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Panama to Improve Infrastructure in Colon Free Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Panama is to invest more than
3.5 million U.S. dollars in improving the infrastructure in its
Colon Free Zone (CFZ).
</P>
<P>
The investment, approved on Tuesday by the National Executive
Council (NEC), will place the CFZ in a better position to compete
with other free zones in the region, said the local press on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The NEC also gave the go-ahead to the Fire Department to allow
fire-fighting crews to act in the free zone.
</P>
<P>
The CFZ, established 51 years ago, boasts some 12 billion
dollars a year in duty free imports and re-exports, making it the
hemisphere's biggest free zone and the single biggest part of
Panama's economy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
