<HEADLINE> WEF Summit Opens With Kosovo Issue on Agenda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, June 30 (Xinhua) -- A summit of central and eastern
European countries, which will be dominated by the Kosovo issue,
opened in the Austrian city of Salzburg Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The World Economic Forum (WEF) regional meeting will also
discuss the enlargement of the European Union and review the
drastic changes which began ten years ago in the former Soviet
Union and the eastern European countries.
</P>
<P>
Presidents and prime ministers from 16 central and eastern
European states as well as some businessmen attended the three-day
summit, the fourth such annual meeting.
</P>
<P>
Also at the summit were representatives of some international
organizations, including UN High Commissioner for Refugees Sadako
Ogata. 
</P>
</TEXT>
