<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cuba to Host Ibero-American Education Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The forthcoming Ibero-American
Conference of Education Ministers will discuss new challenges to
education in the globalization process, Cuban Education Minister
Luis Ignacio Gomez said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, the ninth of its kind, is scheduled to start here
on Thursday and to be attended by education ministers or their
representatives from more than 20 countries in the Ibero-American
community.
</P>
<P>
The central theme of the meeting is "education quality," its
development and integration in the face of globalization, Gomez
said. He added that a "Havana Declaration" will be adopted at the
end of the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The participants will discuss education problems in Latin
America, where the official number of illiterate population stands
at 43 million and only four percent of the gross domestic product
is spent on education. 
</P>
</TEXT>
