<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UNCHR Envoy Calls for Halt to Attacks Against Minorities in Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, June 30 (Xinhua) -- UNCHR Special Envoy Dennis McNamara
Wednesday called on the returned refugees in Kosovo to stop
attacking the Serb and Gypsy population in Kosovo, the Albanian
Telegraphic Agency (ATA) reported.
</P>
<P>
ATA quoted the UNCHR (U.N. High Commissioner for Refugees)
office in Tirana as saying that McNamara indicated that there were
"reports of threats and violent attacks against the Serb and Gypsy
minorities in Kosovo" during the past two weeks and the envoy
requested these actions should end.
</P>
<P>
McNamara also urged the international peace keeping forces in
Kosovo to take security measures to protect the minority
population in Kosovo according to the United Nations Security
Council Resolution 1244, ATA said.
</P>
<P>
Other reports said many returned Albanian refugees wantonly
plundered the property of the Serb and other minorities in Kosovo
and burned their houses as soon as they came back. As the disarmed
Kosovo Liberation Army backs them up, the ethnic Albanians have
nothing more to fear and hundreds of thousands of Serbs have fled
Kosovo for fear of revenge by ethnic Albanians, the reports said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
